The paper deals with the reachability problem in a distributed system, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of stochastic schedulers and the study of non-determinism suggest that the paper may also belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The use of automata and protocols suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) category. The study of the system as a network suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. Finally, the use of algorithms to solve the problem suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
